---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/sections/Section.astro';
import CTABanner from '../../components/sections/CTABanner.astro';
import Card from '../../components/ui/Card.astro';
import Button from '../../components/ui/Button.astro';
import ScrollReveal from '../../components/animation/ScrollReveal.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Business Owners | IBC Academy"
  description="You built a business that generates real wealth. But there's a function inside it generating even more — and you're giving it away. 6 articles that change how you think about capital."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <Section background="cream">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <span class="hero-eyebrow">For Business Owners & Entrepreneurs</span>
        <h1 class="hero-title">You Built a Business. <br />Now It's Time to Build a Bank.</h1>
        <p class="hero-text">
          You understand cash flow. You know what it feels like to need capital on a Tuesday and hear "we'll get back to you in two weeks." You've watched a credit line disappear at the worst possible moment.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-text">
          Your business is a wealth engine. But there's a function inside it — the financing function — that generates more profit than most operations ever will. And right now, you're handing that profit to someone else.
        </p>
        <p class="hero-text">
          These six articles won't waste your time. No theory. No fluff. Just a clear look at how business owners are taking control of their own capital — and why every business should become its own bank.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- What This Is (And Isn't) -->
  <Section title="What This Journey Is (And Isn't)">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="clarity-content">
        <div class="clarity-grid">
          <div class="clarity-box">
            <h3 class="clarity-heading is-not">This is NOT:</h3>
            <ul class="clarity-list">
              <li>A pitch to dump your business and sell insurance</li>
              <li>A "hack" or creative financing gimmick</li>
              <li>A replacement for smart business operations</li>
              <li>Something that works without capitalization and discipline</li>
              <li>A shortcut around building a real business</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="clarity-box">
            <h3 class="clarity-heading is-yes">This IS:</h3>
            <ul class="clarity-list">
              <li>A way to recapture the financing cost inside your business</li>
              <li>Capital you control — no applications, no approvals</li>
              <li>A system that gets stronger every year you operate</li>
              <li>The same principle banks use, applied to your operation</li>
              <li>Practical education built for people who run things</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="clarity-footer">
          By the end, you'll either see a second business hiding inside your first — or you'll decide this isn't your path. Either way, you'll understand something most business owners never consider.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- The 6 Articles -->
  <Section title="Your 6-Article Journey" subtitle="Each article takes about 5-7 minutes. Written for operators, not academics. Real scenarios, real numbers." background="cream">
    <div class="journey-grid">
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={0}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-01-greatest-asset" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">Your Business Is Your Greatest Asset (Right?)</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">You built something real. It generates wealth. But there's a function inside your business that generates even more — and you're giving it away.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={100}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-02-cash-flow-problem" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">The Cash Flow Problem Nobody Talks About</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Seasonal swings. Receivables gaps. That moment when you need capital NOW but the bank says "two weeks." Sound familiar?</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={200}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-03-banking-business" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">Every Business Is Already in the Banking Business</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">Nelson Nash's grocery store analogy reveals something hiding in plain sight: your business already performs the banking function. The question is who profits from it.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={300}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-04-what-banks-cost" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">04</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">What Banks Really Cost Your Business</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">It's not just the interest rate. It's the approval delays, the collateral requirements, the credit lines pulled at the worst moment. The real cost is opportunity.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={400}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-05-banks-itself" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">05</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">The Business That Banks Itself</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">What if you had a pool of capital you controlled — no applications, no approvals, no collateral? Here's how IBC creates that for business owners.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal direction="up" delay={500}>
        <a href="/learn/articles/business-06-two-businesses" class="journey-card-link">
          <div class="journey-card">
            <span class="journey-number">06</span>
            <h3 class="journey-title">Two Businesses, One Owner</h3>
            <p class="journey-desc">The most successful IBC practitioners run two businesses: their primary operation AND their banking operation. Here's why — and how to start.</p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Why This Matters -->
  <Section title="Why Bother?">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="why-content">
        <p class="why-text">
          Think about every van you've financed. Every piece of equipment. Every line of credit you tapped to cover payroll during a slow month.
        </p>
        <blockquote class="why-quote">
          "You finance everything you buy. Either you pay interest to someone else, or you give up the interest you could have earned."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="why-attribution">— Nelson Nash, creator of the Infinite Banking Concept</p>
        <p class="why-text">
          As a business owner, you don't just finance purchases — you finance operations. Constantly. The financing function never stops.
        </p>
        <p class="why-text">
          An HVAC contractor who buys a new van every four years pays $45,000 in interest over twenty years — just to keep working. A wholesaler who needs capital in 72 hours can't wait for bank approvals. A practice owner financing equipment is writing checks to a lender when that money could be recirculating through their own system.
        </p>
        <p class="why-text">
          The question isn't whether your business needs financing. It's whether you'll control that function — or keep giving it away.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <Section background="cream">
    <ScrollReveal direction="up">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <h2 class="cta-title">Ready to Start?</h2>
        <p class="cta-text">
          Article 1 takes about 5 minutes. No signup. No email capture. Just a straight look at the asset you've built — and the one you're missing.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-button">
          <Button variant="primary" size="lg" href="/learn/articles/business-01-greatest-asset">
            Begin Article 1 →
          </Button>
        </div>
        <p class="cta-note">
          Running a business means you're short on time. These articles respect that. Read one now, come back for the rest when you're ready.
        </p>
      </div>
    </ScrollReveal>
  </Section>

  <!-- Final Note -->
  <CTABanner
    heading="Talk to Other Business Owners"
    description="Join our free community where business owners, practitioners, and entrepreneurs discuss IBC implementation. Real questions. Real answers."
    buttonText="Join the Conversation"
    buttonHref="https://skool.com/ibc-academy"
  />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section */
  .hero-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .hero-title {
      font-size: 3rem;
    }
  }

  .hero-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .hero-text:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Clarity Section */
  .clarity-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .clarity-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .clarity-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .clarity-box {
    background: var(--color-cream, #FAF9F6);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .clarity-heading {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .clarity-heading.is-not {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
  }

  .clarity-heading.is-yes {
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
  }

  .clarity-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .clarity-list li {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .clarity-list li::before {
    content: "•";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
  }

  .clarity-footer {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Journey Section */
  .journey-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .journey-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .journey-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .journey-card-link {
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
  }

  .journey-card {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.08);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .journey-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(27, 42, 74, 0.12);
  }

  .journey-number {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .journey-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .journey-desc {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Why Section */
  .why-content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .why-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .why-quote {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem 0;
    padding: 0 1rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold, #C9A962);
    text-align: left;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .why-quote {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      padding: 0 2rem;
    }
  }

  .why-attribution {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
    text-align: left;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .why-attribution {
      padding-left: 2rem;
    }
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-content {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-navy, #1B2A4A);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .cta-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
  }

  .cta-button {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-note {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, #5A6B8A);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
